The President spoke with Chancellor Merkel about Ukraine. They welcomed the conclusions of the European Council and the unified position of the US and EU regarding Ukraine. They agreed on the need for Russia to pull back its forces, allow international observers and human rights monitors in Crimea, and support free and fair elections in May. They discussed the need for Russia to agree on a contact group for direct dialogue between Ukraine and Russia to de-escalate the situation and restore Ukraine's territorial integrity. They expressed concern over Russia's violation of international law through its military intervention in Ukraine.